# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different OS, they may override each other.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   According to poetry documentation, poetry.lock file should be tracked in version control.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   According to pdm documentation, pdm.lock file should be tracked in version control.
# pdm.lock

